{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117730,"nonce":"2ATjrvO7ViKqd8CV/BTXc95Eu/0=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLpWCzwAAAAVhP-V0"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772119002,"nonce":"aESUbvZplCaICbXtJJzem4k7Y20=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sd_C_","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/277#issuecomment-3967283391"},"message":"## Design note: triage output should be a comment, not an issue edit\n\nDuring the #272 triage we considered whether findings should update the issue body or be posted as a comment. Decision: **always comment**.\n\n- Editing the issue body loses the paper trail — the original spec becomes invisible\n- A comment preserves triage as a distinct artifact with its own timestamp and author\n- The planning agent can read comments when it starts work\n- The issue body remains the authoritative spec; triage is advisory input\n\nThis should be baked into the skill's instructions: \"Post findings as a comment on the issue. Do not modify the issue body.\"\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772126563,"nonce":"aoRDsM4CWA/h9Ng+/lOlvjfJXg0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sg8Ru","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/277#issuecomment-3968058478"},"message":"I'm wondering if we are using terminology correctly, should triage skill rank the issue in an order while what we want here is an evaluate issue skill or something like that?","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772126705,"nonce":"M46pm/OzPqlNTc+ue9Xurs+sbGU=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87shACI","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/277#issuecomment-3968073864"},"message":"## Triage Report\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — clear deliverable, clear boundaries.\n\n### Naming Question\n\nRoland raised a good point about terminology. \"Triage\" typically implies prioritization/sorting across multiple issues. This skill evaluates a **single issue** against principles and ADRs.\n\nOptions:\n| Name | Pros | Cons |\n|---|---|---|\n| `evaluate-issue` | Most accurate | Verbose |\n| `review-issue` | Pairs with `review-pr`, consistent lifecycle naming | \"Review\" might imply post-implementation |\n| `assess-issue` | Clear meaning | Less familiar |\n| `triage-issue` | Familiar | Implies prioritization, not evaluation |\n\nSuggest `review-issue` for consistency with `review-pr`.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | OK | Single-purpose, no extra features |\n| Human control and transparency | OK | Reports findings, human decides |\n| Capture decisions | OK | Comment-not-edit pattern documented here |\n\n### Concerns\n\n1. **Naming**: See above\n2. **Missing acceptance criterion**: Design note says \"post as comment, don't edit issue body\" — should be an explicit acceptance criterion\n3. **Overlap with plan-task (#278)**: Both evaluate an issue against principles. Boundary: this skill evaluates the *issue itself* (scope, repo placement, ADR conflicts); plan-task evaluates the *implementation plan*. Should be explicit in the skill prompt.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Consider renaming to `review-issue`\n- Add acceptance criterion: \"Posts findings as a comment on the issue\"\n- Clarify boundary with plan-task in the skill prompt\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772142451,"nonce":"ySY0wMNMncfErGjXRY9+6tk1/R0=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uLpWCzwAAAAVh8Z6i"},"status":2}]}